Shaun Andrew McKerry, 31, was arrested after he burst into Shildon Post Office and Stores in County Durham wielding an axe .
But he was foiled when shopkeeper Sab Dhillon heard McKerry's demands and ran from the back of the shop .
He was subdued by a husband and wife duo who rugby tackled him to the floor and his wife appeared to subdue him further .
McKerry pleaded guilty to attempted robbery at Durham Crown Court via videolink from prison .